\p{Let #{\kk / \QQ} be the splitting field of an irreducible monic polynomial #{f(x)\in\ZZ[x]}. Suppose #{p\in\ZZ} is a prime not dividing the discriminant of #{f(x)}.}
\p{Then #{p\ZZ=P_{1}(\dots)P_{r}} is a prime ideal factorization of #{p\ZZ} in #{\AlgInt{\kk}} with #{P_{i}\ideal\AlgInt{\kk}} distinct.}
\p{For each #{P=P_{i}}, the group morphism #{D_{P}\to\Gal(\FF_{q} / \FF_{p})} is an isomorphism. In particular, #{D_{P}} is cyclic of order #{\Index{\FF_{q}}{\FF_{p}}} generated by the Frobenius element in #{\Gal(\FF_{q}/\FF_{p})}.}